<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="387" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1378,1542]" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">
<bibRefCitation box="[151,387,1378,1403]" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" refString="Koeda, K., Yoshino, T., Imai, H. &amp; Tachihara, K. (2014). A review of the genus Pempheris (Perciformes, Pempheridae), with description of a new species. Zootaxa, 3793 (3), 301 - 330. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3793.3.1" type="journal article">
Koeda 
<emphasis box="[237,299,1379,1403]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[320,379,1379,1403]" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" value="2014.0">2014</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
regarded 
<taxonomicName authority="Cuvier" authorityName="Cuvier" box="[511,862,1378,1403]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="malabarica">
<emphasis box="[511,773,1379,1403]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">Pempheris malabarica</emphasis>
Cuvier
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Cuvier. As" authorityName="Cuvier. As" box="[1169,1436,1378,1403]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="molucca">
<emphasis box="[1169,1297,1379,1403]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">P. molucca</emphasis>
Cuvier. 
<collectingCountry box="[1405,1436,1379,1403]" name="American Samoa" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">As</collectingCountry>
</taxonomicName>
discussed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Randall" box="[301,600,1413,1438]" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" refString="Randall, J. E. &amp; Bineesh, K. K. (2014) Review of the fishes of the genus Pempheris (Perciformes: Pempheridae) of India, with description of a new species and a neotype for P. mangula Cuvier. Journal of the Ocean Science Foundation, 10, 20 - 40." type="journal article" year="2014">
Randall &amp; Bineesh (
<number box="[531,592,1414,1438]" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" value="2014.0">2014</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, the name 
<taxonomicName box="[722,846,1413,1437]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="molucca">
<emphasis box="[722,736,1414,1437]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[751,846,1413,1437]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">molucca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on a fanciful painting in Renard from 
<number box="[1380,1436,1414,1438]" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" value="1719.0">1719</number>
and unavailable as a 
<emphasis box="[385,821,1448,1472]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">
nomen dubium. 
<taxonomicName box="[565,821,1448,1472]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pempheridae" genus="Pempheris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="malabarica">Pempheris malabarica</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is a valid species, easily distinguished by having 
<number pageId="10" pageNumber="387" value="45.0" valueMax="48.0" valueMin="42.0">42 to 48</number>
anal soft rays and 
<number box="[398,493,1482,1507]" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" value="70.0" valueMax="75.0" valueMin="65.0">65 to 75</number>
lateral-line scales, the highest for these two counts of Indian Ocean species of the genus (see 
<tableCitation box="[275,369,1517,1542]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,239,528,551]" captionText="TABLE 1. Anal Soft Ray Counts of Species of Pempheris from the Western Indian Ocean." pageId="10" pageNumber="387">
Tables 
<number box="[355,369,1518,1542]" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" value="1.0">1</number>
</tableCitation>
and 
<number box="[423,439,1518,1542]" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" value="3.0">
<tableCitation box="[423,439,1518,1542]" captionStart="TABLE 3" captionStartId="2.[119,198,600,621]" captionText="TABLE 3. Lateral-line Scale Counts of Species of Pempheris from the Western Indian Ocean." pageId="10" pageNumber="387">3</tableCitation>
</number>
).
</paragraph>
